SKILL|findmy|"Track Apple devices/AirTags via FindMy.app on macOS."
STEP|1|**macOS** with Find My app and iCloud signed in
STEP|2|Devices/AirTags already registered in Find My
STEP|3|Screen Recording permission for terminal (System Settings → Privacy → Screen Recording)
STEP|4|**Optional but recommended**: Install `peekaboo` for better UI automation:
STEP|5|User asks "where is my [device/cat/keys/bag]?"
STEP|6|Tracking AirTag locations
STEP|7|Checking device locations (iPhone, iPad, Mac, AirPods)
STEP|8|Monitoring pet or item movement over time (AirTag patrol routes)
STEP|9|FindMy has **no CLI or API** — must use UI automation
STEP|10|AirTags only update location while the FindMy page is actively displayed
STEP|11|Location accuracy depends on nearby Apple devices in the FindMy network
STEP|12|Screen Recording permission required for screenshots
STEP|13|AppleScript UI automation may break across macOS versions
STEP|14|Keep FindMy app in the foreground when tracking AirTags (updates stop when minimized)
STEP|15|Use `vision_analyze` to read screenshot content — don't try to parse pixels
STEP|16|For ongoing tracking, use a cronjob to periodically capture and log locations
STEP|17|Respect privacy — only track devices/items the user owns
